    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-02T16:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-27T05:07:00-05:00" n="412"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/77: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the War Trade Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCormick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">U.S.S. George Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-07-02T16:20:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1919-06-27T15:00:00+04:53">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 2, 1919, 4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have shown your cable<note n="18" xml:id="d412fn18">No. 2441, June 27, 3 p.m., to
                        the Commission to Negotiate Peace, <ref target="#pg_386">p.
                        386</ref>.</note> to the President. He sees no objection to his [Secretary
                    of War] dealing openly with <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>
                    representatives <pb facs="0501" n="389" xml:id="pg_389"/> for the purpose of
                    selling supplies, and no objection to proposed financial plan, provided in both
                    cases there is no formal or diplomatic recognition of the <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> government in accordance with our
                    former cable. [Navy] 2614.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McCormick</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
